#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.48"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.48:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.48:0.2"
msgid "5. Amatavagga"
msgstr "5. The Deathless"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.48:0.3"
msgid "48. Mittasutta"
msgstr "48. Friends"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.189"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.48:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Ye, bhikkhave, anukampeyyātha, ye ca kho sotabbaṃ maññeyyuṃ mittā vā amaccā "
"vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā, te vo, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvanāya "
"samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, those for whom you have sympathy, and those worth listening to—"
"friends and colleagues, relatives and family—should be encouraged, "
"supported, and established in the development of the four kinds of "
"mindfulness meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.48:2.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ, catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn47.48:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.48:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn47.48:2.4"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn47.48:2.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn47.48:2.6"
msgid ""
"Ye, bhikkhave, anukampeyyātha, ye ca sotabbaṃ maññeyyuṃ mittā vā amaccā vā "
"ñātī vā sālohitā vā, te vo, bhikkhave, imesaṃ catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ "
"bhāvanāya samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Those for whom you have sympathy, and those worth listening to—friends and "
"colleagues, relatives and family—should be encouraged, supported, and "
"established in the development of the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.48:2.7"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
